other_tests.findings: Status post cholecystectomy with surgical clips in the gallbladder fossa. High-density fluid in the gallbladder fossa, perihepatic and subhepatic areas, measuring up to 70 Hounsfield units, with no active extravasation.

Moderate atelectasis in the dependent areas of bilateral lung bases, high-density fluid in the gallbladder fossa and surrounding areas, and a moderate amount of free fluid in the pelvis. No evidence of focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, or kidneys.
